title: 🦩 "If you spend too much time thinking about a thing, you'll never get it done." - Bruce Lee
content:
Given an array of random integers, move all the zeros in the array to the end of the array. Try to keep this in O(n) time (or better)!

Example:

$ moveZeros([1, 2, 0, 1, 0, 0, 3, 6]) $ [1, 2, 1, 3, 6, 0, 0, 0]
